      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "A win looks imminent for GOLDEN SUNSET (1) who has clocked in second in her last four outings here, last week coming from a 30m handicap and racing wide in the latter stages before going under narrowly. Her record at this shorter distance is good and she gets her chance from the inside barrier. NOT AS PROMISED (4) started from the same mark as GOLDEN SUNSET last week and was less than 3m behind her after racing parked. Beat that rival in winning prior and he is suited back to this distance having won four of the five times he has attempted it here. Big chance. ZEALOUS SPUR NZ (5) started 10m in front of the top-two selections under the handicap conditions last week but did well to beat them for a narrow win. Draws outside that pair but must be respected. MUFASA METRO NZ (3) is an accomplished trotter resuming off trial win. Hasn't missed a place at this distance and draws well so keep safe.",
